{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/writing-resources/awesome-scientific-writing/week/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"writing-resources/awesome-scientific-writing","descriptionHTML":"<div>\n<g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"keyboard\" fallback-src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/2328.png\">⌨️</g-emoji> A curated list of awesome tools, demos and resources to go beyond LaTeX </div>","description":":keyboard: A curated list of awesome tools, demos and resources to go beyond LaTeX "},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-29T11:34:45.276Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jupyterbook.org/\">Jupyter Book</a> - A static site generator which converts\na collection of CommonMark, MyST markdown and Jupyter notebooks into a HTML website.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-29T16:26:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://myst-parser.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">MyST</a> - Markedly Structured Text,\na superset of CommonMark markdown with reStructuredText like features.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-29T16:26:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate/#readme\">Pandoc Markdown-LaTeX\nBoilerplate</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">89</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":89,\"repo\":\"davecap/markdown-latex-boilerplate\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Demonstrate\nhow to integrate Pandoc with an existing LaTeX template which\nrequires some boilerplate code (i.e. LaTeX preamble), thus avoiding the\n<code>latexmk</code> dependency.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-24T15:16:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://editor.citationstyles.org/\">Citation Style Language (CSL) styles</a> - Crowdsourced\nrepository with over 9000 free CSL citation styles and an online\neditor to create new ones.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T10:03:13.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pandoc.org/MANUAL\">pandoc</a> - Haskell library for converting from\none markup format to another, and a command-line tool that uses this\nlibrary 🔖 🔗.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/smathot/academicmarkdown#readme\">Academic Markdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/smathot/academicmarkdown#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">323</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":323,\"repo\":\"smathot/academicmarkdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Python wrapper over Pandoc with specialized extensions to parse certain\nelements, making it a superset of Pandoc Markdown flavour 🔖\n🔗.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jgm/pandoc/wiki/Pandoc-Filters\">Pandoc filters</a> - List of\naddons to pandoc which implement extra features such as citations and\ncross-references.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://scorreia.com/software/panflute/\">Panflute</a> - Pythonic alternative\nto John MacFarlane's pandocfilters.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\">Eisvogel</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3238,\"repo\":\"Wandmalfarbe/pandoc-latex-template\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Clean academic pandoc LaTeX template.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://u.arizona.edu/~selisker/post/workflow/\">Scott Selisker</a> - Plain Text Workflow for Academic Writing with Atom.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T09:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://zbib.org/\">ZoteroBib</a> - Online bibliography reference manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T08:23:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Spell Checking and Linting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://aspell.net/\">GNU Aspell</a> - Command line spell checker.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-08T11:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Spell Checking and Linting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://hunspell.github.io/\">Hunspell</a> - Command line spell checker.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-08T11:09:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://atom.io\">Atom</a> - Popular IDE with Markdown support.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/shd101wyy/markdown-preview-enhanced\">Markdown Preview Enhanced for Atom</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/shd101wyy/markdown-preview-enhanced\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3210,\"repo\":\"shd101wyy/markdown-preview-enhanced\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pandoc\nintegration and utilities for Atom.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/apcshields/autocomplete-bibtex\">Autocomplete BibTeX for Atom</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/apcshields/autocomplete-bibtex\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">44</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":44,\"repo\":\"apcshields/autocomplete-bibtex\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - BibTeX support for Atom.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://marktext.app/\">Marktext</a> - Markdown text editor.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/rstudio\">R Studio</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/rstudio\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3626,\"repo\":\"rstudio/rstudio\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - IDE for R.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/bookdown\">bookdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/bookdown\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2457,\"repo\":\"rstudio/bookdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - R package to facilitate writing books and long-form articles, reports with R Markdown 🔖 🔗.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/\">R Markdown</a> - R package to write R next to Markdown</li>\n</ul>\n🔖\n🔗.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.vim.org/\">Vim</a> - Command line text editor.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/msprev/fzf-bibtex/#readme\">fzf-bibtex</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/msprev/fzf-bibtex/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">60</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":60,\"repo\":\"msprev/fzf-bibtex\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - BibTeX source\nwith Vim integration which uses fzf (a fuzzy finder implemented in Go).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc\">vim-pandoc</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">749</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":749,\"repo\":\"vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pandoc integration and utilities for Vim.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc-syntax\">vim-pandoc-syntax</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc-syntax\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">317</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":317,\"repo\":\"vim-pandoc/vim-pandoc-syntax\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Pandoc syntax highlighting for Vim.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">Visual Studio Code</a> - Popular IDE with Markdown support.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown/#readme\">Markdown All in One</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1912,\"repo\":\"yzhang-gh/vscode-markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Extension for enhanced\nMarkdown support in VSCode, such as preview and auto completion to name a few.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Word Processors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zettlr.com/\">Zettlr</a> - Markdown editor which\nintegrates CSL, BibLaTeX, Pandoc and many other tools\n🔖 🔗.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.jabref.org/\">JabRef</a> - Open source bibliography reference manager.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Bibliography</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/\">Zotero</a> - FOSS tool to collect, organize, cite, and\nshare research.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://retorque.re/zotero-better-bibtex/\">Better BibTeX for Zotero</a> - Enhanced\nBibTeX / BibLaTeX integration for Zotero.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://zotfile.com/\">ZotFile for Zotero</a> - Enhanced PDF file management for Zotero.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.diagrams.net/\">diagrams.net</a> - Open source, online, desktop and\ncontainer deployable diagramming software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://graphviz.org/\">graphviz</a> - Visualization software for graphs and\nnetworks which uses a domain-specific DOT language.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid-live-editor/\">Mermaid Live Editor</a> - Define simple diagrams instead of drawing them.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://vega.github.io/vega-lite/examples/\">Vega Lite</a> - Define charts and more complex diagrams.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Illustrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://plantuml.com/\">PlantUML</a> - Define UML diagrams instead of drawing them.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates/\">Steve's R Markdown Templates</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">695</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":695,\"repo\":\"svmiller/svm-r-markdown-templates\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Academic manuscript, memos, Beamer presentation, syllabus and CV.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://programminghistorian.org/en/lessons/sustainable-authorship-in-plain-text-using-pandoc-and-markdown\">Dennis Tenen and Grant Wythoff</a> - Sustainable Authorship in Plain Text using Pandoc and Markdown.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T20:49:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Articles</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/JensErat/scientific-markdown/#readme\">scientific-markdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JensErat/scientific-markdown/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">32</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":32,\"repo\":\"JensErat/scientific-markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Example\nfor use of Markdown for scientific publications using Pandoc and\n<code>latexmk</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Presentations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jez/pandoc-starter/#readme\">pandoc-starter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jez/pandoc-starter/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">449</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":449,\"repo\":\"jez/pandoc-starter\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Templates for\narticles, Beamer presentations etc. using Markdown files and Makefiles for\ngetting started with Pandoc.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Presentations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cgroll/slides/#readme\">slides</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cgroll/slides/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"cgroll/slides\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Demo for generating <code>reveal.js</code>\npresentations using Pandoc.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/bookdown-demo/#readme\">bookdown-demo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rstudio/bookdown-demo/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">341</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":341,\"repo\":\"rstudio/bookdown-demo\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Minimal\nexample of a book based on R Markdown and bookdown.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Templates</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/tompollard/phd_thesis_markdown#readme\">Template for writing a PhD thesis in\nMarkdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/tompollard/phd_thesis_markdown#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">916</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":916,\"repo\":\"tompollard/phd_thesis_markdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Clean\norganization of files to provide a framework for writing a PhD thesis in\nmostly Markdown with a little bit of LaTeX, and compiled with Pandoc.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/clawpack/riemann_book/#readme\">Book on Riemann solvers</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/clawpack/riemann_book/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">160</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":160,\"repo\":\"clawpack/riemann_book\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This\nexample uses a custom <code>nbconvert</code> template and shows how to store your\nnotebooks with no output (for version control) while automatically executing\nthem before running <code>bookbook</code>, so that PDF and HTML versions include the\noutput.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/katrinleinweber/PhD-thesis/#readme\">Katrin Leinweber's Ph.D.\nthesis</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/katrinleinweber/PhD-thesis/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">25</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":25,\"repo\":\"katrinleinweber/PhD-thesis\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Automated\nwork flow involving several tools, but primarily Pandoc, <code>latexmk</code> and\nAcademic Markdown.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jupyter4edu/jupyter-edu-book/#readme\">Teaching and learning with\nJupyter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jupyter4edu/jupyter-edu-book/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">333</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":333,\"repo\":\"jupyter4edu/jupyter-edu-book\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Book\nwritten in R Markdown, bookdown and also rendered as HTML, PDF and\nEPUB.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.draketo.de/english/emacs/writing-papers-in-org-mode-acpd\">Writing scientific papers for ACPD using Emacs\nOrg-mode</a> - Detailed\ntutorial on authoring a paper by seamlessly integrating with LaTeX\ncommands within Org-mode.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-07T16:27:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://docutils.sourceforge.io/docs/\">docutils</a> - Python package which can\nconvert reStructuredText into various formats and provides command-line\ntools to do it 🔗.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-21T13:18:53.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cicero.xyz/\">Cicero</a> - Python package which renders HTML presentations\nfrom Markdown source using remark or reveal.js 🔗.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-20T18:05:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Converters and Filters</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nbconvert.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">nbconvert</a> - Convert Jupyter\nnotebooks into <code>reveal.js</code> presentations, PDF, HTML, Markdown,\nreStructuredText and more.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/takluyver/bookbook/#readme\">bookbook</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/takluyver/bookbook/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">88</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":88,\"repo\":\"takluyver/bookbook\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Experimental Python\npackage which extends <code>nbconvert</code> and adds the ability to cross reference\nwithin and across notebooks 🔗.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/chrisjsewell/ipypublish/#readme\">ipypublish</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/chrisjsewell/ipypublish/#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">194</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":194,\"repo\":\"chrisjsewell/ipypublish\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Workflow for\ncreating and editing publication ready scientific reports and presentations,\nfrom one or more Jupyter Notebooks, without leaving the browser 🔖\n🔗.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-07T07:44:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Spell Checking and Linting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://languagetool.org/\">LanguageTool</a> - Open source grammar, style and</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-07T07:44:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Awesome Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/markusschanta/awesome-jupyter/#renderingpublishingconversion\">Jupyter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/markusschanta/awesome-jupyter/#renderingpublishingconversion\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-ri